HEADWORD: Serenely
<hw>Se*rene"ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In a serene
manner; clearly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Now setting Ph⟦oe⟧bus shone <qex>serenely</qex> bright.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>With unruffled temper; coolly; calmly.</def>
<rj><au>Prior.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sereneness</ent>⟦br⟧
